<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Documenting quality requirements</title>
    <para>
        <indexterm><primary>quality requirements</primary><secondary>documenting</secondary></indexterm>
        <indexterm><primary>quality requirements</primary><secondary>quantifying</secondary></indexterm>
        Quality requirements are usually documented in text. They should be specified as precisely as possible and should
        preferably be quantified. When quantifying quality requirements it is important to specify the units used.
    </para>
</section>
